-- Tempo Group, Leuliette to Form Investment Firm Focusing on Auto Industry
-- B y   M a r k   C l o t h i e r
-- 2010-12-14T15:38:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/tempo-group-leuliette-to-form-investment-firm-focusing-on-auto-industry.html
Tempo Group  and Leuliette Partners
LLC said they will form an investment firm to seek mergers,
acquisitions and restructurings in the automotive and
transportation industries.  The venture will focus on businesses that make chassis,
powertrains, bodies, special vehicles, energy technologies and
related components, the companies said today in a statement
distributed by PR Newswire. The agreement will be completed this
year, the companies said.  Tempo Group, a Chinese company whose North American
headquarters is in Canton, Michigan, said today it completed the
purchase of steering-systems producer Nexteer with an affiliate
of the Beijing government from  General Motors Co . for $450
million.  Leuliette Partners, based in Birmingham, Michigan, is run
by  Tim Leuliette , a former chief executive officer of  Metaldyne
Corp .  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Mark Clothier  in Southfield, Michigan, at 
 mclothier@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jamie Butters at   jbutters@bloomberg.net . 